OL,3,CEx-GP jailed for sex offences against
OL,4,Cpatients including two teenage boys
OL,6,FThe judge added: "The abuse of trust
OL,7,Fhere is immense. People trusted you
OL,8,Fwith access to their bodies and you
OL,9,Fabused that trust for your own sexual
OL,10,Fgratification.
OL,12,F"You were able to construct a false
OL,13,Fdefence to justify your sexual
OL,14,Fassaults because that is something
OL,15,Fthat is very easy for a GP to do.
OL,17,F"Your exploitative actions betrayed
OL,18,Fnot only patients, but your wider
OL,19,Fprofession."
