OL,3,CEx-GP jailed for sex offences against
OL,4,Cpatients including two teenage boys
OL,6,F"Your victims are no longer silent,
OL,7,Fand your legacy is not the doctor who
OL,8,Fhelped people, it's the harm you
OL,9,Fcaused when no-one was watching."
OL,11,FAddressing Manson, he said: "You
OL,12,Ftaught me that help isn't always safe,
OL,13,Fthat authority can betray, and trust
OL,14,Fcan be dangerous."
OL,16,FDuring the trial, the prosecution
OL,17,Fnoted that "many examinations he
OL,18,Fperformed were not medically
OL,19,Fjustified" and that other GPs would
OL,20,Fnot have carried them out.
